paragraphs.text: west side, east side little willy willy wears the crown,-- he's the king around town-- dancing, glancing-- willy drives them silly,-- with his star shoe shimmy shuffle down--
way past one, and feeling allright-- 'cos with little willy round-- they can last all night-- hey down, stay down,-- stay down down--
'cos little willy, willy won't go home-- but you can't push willy round-- willy won't go,-- try tellin' everybody but, oh no-- little willy, willy won't go home--
up town, down town-- little willy, willy drives them wild-- with his runaround style-- inside, outside-- willy sends them silly with his-- starshine shimmy shuffle smile--
mama done chase-- willy down through the hall-- but laugh, willy laugh,-- he don't care at all-- hey down, stay down, stay down, down--
